import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What is the trend of price over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['hour'] = data['date'].dt.hour
    data['minute'] = data['date'].dt.minute
    data['second'] = data['date'].dt.second
    data['time'] = data['hour'] + data['minute']/60 + data['second']/3600
    sns.barplot(x='time', y='price', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Price: {:.2f}'.format(data['price'].mean()))
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.title('What is the average price?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of price?')
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['price'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='price', data=data, ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.set_title('What is the highest and lowest price?')
    ax.axvline(data['price'].min(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Minimum price: {data["price"].min():.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['price'].max(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Maximum price: {data["price"].max():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
